					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 17.0, 59.0, 720.0, 47.0 ],
					"text" : "Maps an input to the first inlet to a continuous sigmoid/logit function (S or sideways-S curve) using the logistic approach using the transcendental function exp. The steepness of the S curve in both cases can be defined with a parameter in the second inlet. A second parameter defines a shift along either the x-axis or y-axis for more flexibility, depending if a>0 (sigmoid) or a<0 (logit)."
				}

